HISTORY SOUTHERN OBSERVATORY: IN THAT PROCESS, FLAGS THAT INDICATE SATURATIONS  HISTORY BAD PIXELS, RESEAU MARKS, COSMIC RAY EVENTS, ETC... WERE LOST (SEE THE  HISTORY LAST PARAGRAPH OF COMMENTS).                                            COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT PROC FILE ARCH:[FESTOU]B00155.REC;1                                     COMMENT OBJECT  = '4 LWP  8078     '            / THE IDENTIFIER                COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT THE INTERNATIONAL ULTRAVIOLET EXPLORER OBSERVATORY IS A SPACE BORNE     COMMENT TELESCOPE, WITH AN APERTURE OF 45 CM, IN GEOSYCHRONOUS ORBIT, OVER      COMMENT THE APPROXIMATE GEOGRAPHIC LATITUDE AND LONGITUDE, GIVEN IN THE         COMMENT LAT--OBS AND LONG-OBS KEYWORDS. THE SEMI-MAJOR AXIS OF THE ORBIT IS     COMMENT 42,152 KM WITH PERIGEE AT 32,050 KM.  THE ELEV-OBS KEYWORD IS SET TO    COMMENT -9999.9 TO INDICATE THAT THE OBSERVATIONS WERE OBTAINED FROM AN EARTH   COOMENT ORBITING SPACECRAFT. ACTUAL MEAN ELEVATION IN METERS (ELEV-OBS) IS      COMMENT APPROXIMATELY 42,000,000 +-10,000,000 METERS AND CAN BE RETRIEVED.      COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT DETAILED DESCRIPTION OF THE IUE CAN BE FOUND IN THE NASA AND ESA IUE    COMMENT NEWSLETTERS PUBLISHED SINCE 1978.  NOTE IN PARTICULAR THAT THE          COMMENT CHARACTERISTICS OF THE IUE SPECTROGRAPHS ARE GIVEN IN THE NASA          COMMENT NEWSLETTER #18 (PANEK ET AL.), CASSATELLA ET AL. (ASTRON. ASTROPHYS.    COMMENT 1985, 144, 335) AND IN PEREZ ET AL. (NASA NEWSLETTER #43). THE JULY     COMMENT 1987 (#32) ISSUE OF THE NASA IUE NEWSLETTERS PROVIDES INFORMATION ON    COMMENT THE CONVERSION OF IUE RAW DATA NUMBERS INTO ABSOLUTE FLUX UNITS.  A     COMMENT GENERAL DESCRIPTION OF THE IUE CAN BE FOUND IN NATURE, 275, 5 OCTOBER   COMMENT 1978, PAGE 372. ONE SHOULD OBSERVE THAT COMETS ARE EXTENDED SOURCES AN  COMMENT THAT CONSEQUENTLY RESOLUTIONS ARE SERIOUSLY DEGRADED. DRIFTING MOTIONS  COMMENT MAY FURTHER DEGRADE THE RESOLUTION. ABSOLUTE CALIBRATIONS ARE STRICTLY  COMMENT VALID FOR POINT SOURCES. THE ERROR ATTACHED TO MOST COMET EMISION FLUX  COMMENT IS OF THE ORDER OF 10%.                                                 COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT SKY EXPOSURES ARE NOT IDENTIFIED AS SUCH. THE VALUE OF PARAMETER SEPNU  COMMENT SHOULD ALLOW ONE TO IDENTIFY THOSE SPECTRA USUALLY RECORDED 2 DEGREES   COMMENT SUNWARD.                                                                COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT KEYWORD 'TIME-OBS' TAKES INTO ACCOUNT, WHEN POSSIBLE, THE FACT THAT     COMMENT SOME EXPOSURES WERE TAKEN IN MULTIPLE SEGMENTS.                         COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT THE COMMENT OBJECT PSEUDO-KEYWORD CONTAINS THE IUE IMAGE NUMBERS        COMMENT OF THE SPECTRA. A NUMERAL IN FRONT OF THE IUE IMAGE NUMBER INDICATES    COMMENT A RAW IUE IMAGE IF SET TO 3, A CALIBRATED LINE BY LINE SPECTRUM IF      COMMENT SET TO 4. IMAGES '4 LWPXXXX L' AND '4 LWPXXXX S' ARE EXTRACTED FROM TH  COMMENT SAME RAW IMAGE: THEY ARE SIMPLY SHIFTED TO PUT EITHER THE LARGE OR      COMMENT THE SMALL SLIT NEAR THE CENTER OF THE FIELD. THE MENTION 'FLUX (L OR    COMMENT S)' THAT MAY APPEAR AFTER AN IUE IMAGE NUMBER INDICATES FLUX            COMMENT CALIBRATED DATA FOR EITHER THE LARGE OR THE SMALL SLIT; AS FOR LINE     COMMENT BY LINE SPECTRA, UNITS ARE 1E-14 ERGS/CM**2/A/SEC. WHEN THE IMAGE IS    COMMENT A RAW IUE IMAGE, THE DEPENDENT VARIABLE IS EXPRESSED IN 'IUE DATA       COMMENT NUMBERS' (I.E. BETWEEN 0 AND 255).                                      COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT QUALITY OF THE DATA IS DIFFICULT TO ASSESS. MOST SPECTRA ARE EXPOSED    COMMENT TO REVEAL OR/AND MEASURE SPECIFIC FEATURES (USUALLY, OH 0-0 AND LYMAN-  COMMENT ALPHA IN SHORT LWP AND SWP EXPOSURES, RESPECTIVELY; OTHER WEAKER        COMMENT FEATURES IN LONGER ONES).                                               COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT EXPOSURE TIMES MAY NOT BE EXACTLY THOSE MENTIONED HERE: SOMETIMES, THE  COMMENT HISTORY OF THE MOTION OF THE SLIT DURING THE OBSERVATIONS IS QUITE      COMMENT COMPLEX, DUE TO DRIFTS. A COMPREHENSIVE DESCRIPTION OF THE              COMMENT CIRCUMSTANCES IN WHICH THE IUE OBSERVATIONS WERE OBTAINED IS GIVEN      COMMENT IN FESTOU, 1990, ESA-SP 1134 (192 PAGES). THIS DOCUMENT IS ABSOLUTELY   COMMENT REQUIRED TO MAKE A CORRECT USE OF THE OBSERVATIONS AND INTERPRET THE    COMMENT FLUX MEASUREMENTS (STRONGLY AFFECTED BY EVENTUAL DRIFTS OF THE          COMMENT SPACECRAFT DURING THE OBSERVATIONS). SATURATED FEATURES ARE INDICATED   COMMENT AS WELL AS DRIFTING MOTIONS. FINE ERROR SENSOR COUNT RATES ARE ALSO     COMMENT GIVEN.                                                                  COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT                                                                         COMMENT EACH INDIVIDUAL OBSERVATION SHOULD LEAD TO THE PRODUCTION OF 4          COMMENT FILES (LOW RESOLUTION SPECTRA) OR TO ABOUT 10 FILES (HIGH DISPERSION    COMMENT SPECTRA). IN THIS ARCHIVE, SOME FILES ARE MISSING (PROCESSING NOT       COMMENT REQUESTED BY OBSERVER OR NOT SUBMITTED TO THE ARCHIVE BECAUSE THEY      COMMENT WERE NOT AVAILABLE AT TIME OF SUBMISSION). ABOUT 20 LINE BY LINE        COMMENT IMAGES AND A FEW EXTRACTED SPECTRA ARE MISSING.                         COMMENT LOW RESOLUTION DATA CONSISTS IN MOST CASES OF ONE TYPE "4" IMAGE        COMMENT (A LINE BY LINE IMAGE) AND OF ONE OR TWO EXTRACTED SPECTRA OBTAINED     COMMENT THROUGH THE LARGE AND/OR SMALL SLIT (MENTIONS 'L' AND 'S' FOLLOW THE    COMMENT FILE NUMBER. UNITS ARE ERG/CM**2/S/A OR 1E-14 ERG/CM**2/S/A             COMMENT (MINIMA AND MAXIMA OF FLUX VALUES AS WELL AS BS AND BZERO FACTORS       COMMENT ALLOW TO DISTINGUISH BETWEEN THE TWO CASES).                            COMMENT IN HIGH RESOLTION MODE, DATA CONSITS OF A TYPE "3" IMAGE (THE           COMMENT RAW IMAGE) AND A SERIES OF EXTRACTED SPECTRA CENTERED AROUND            COMMENT WAVELENGTHS WHERE SPECTRAL FEATURES ARE KNOWN TO EXIST. UNITS           COMMENT ARE IUE DATA NUMBERS (BETWEEN 0 AND 255) FOR RAW IMAGES AND             COMMENT 1E-14 ERG/CM**2/S/A FOR THE EXTRACTED SPECTRA.                          COMMENT                                                                         END                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             